channel.title: Wcing problem!
channel.description: [b]hey guys i am working on a blank source , and i am farely new at coding, i am working on a wcing base atm, and whenever i cut the logs it gives me coins instead of logs, does any one know how i can replace this is the correct logs for each tree?[/b] thanks gusy! ~~~Mock Pro~~~

item.title: Wcing problem!
item.dc:creator: @The_Outsider The Outsider
item.description:
@The_Outsider wrote:

You only need to restart your server when editing .cfg files as the compiler doesn’t compile them. You’re probably missing a few directories. Use RuneSource’s compiler (with the javac++.jar file in the libs folder) created by blakeman8192, it automatically finds all directories without you having to declare them.

item.title: Wcing problem!
item.dc:creator: @imsuperman05 imsuperman05
item.description:
@imsuperman05 wrote:

[quote=“The Outsider, post:5, topic:421308”][quote author=tyb97 link=topic=523971.msg3812509#msg3812509 date=1321057054]

yes very easy go to your config and type woodcutting don’t add the * then look for the wcing skill and it should say 995 but add the log idea that u want to make the tree give u and there u go

This is not a PI he said blank.

Find your Woodcutting class and look for 995 (the coin ID) and replace it with the log ID. Self explanatory really, post your class/method that handles Woodcutting if you get stuck.

“Blank” could mean PI derp derp… but yeah, do what these 2 said.
[/quote]
It shouldn’t mean PI though.[/quote]
It isn’t blank because he can’t even change what’s being given for woodcutting.
